18:44.100 --> 18:46.300
getting it clear, clean after weapons.

18:46.300 --> 18:51.260
You don't want to take back bullets that maybe got rusted or maybe got jammed or hit around

18:51.260 --> 18:53.540
while you're going through the jungle getting off helicopters.

18:53.540 --> 18:57.580
So we pretty much clean our weapons and then re-supply ourselves when we got back to the

18:57.580 --> 18:58.580
base camp.

18:58.580 --> 19:01.420
Now naturally we would use all our ammunition at this point because you never know when

19:01.420 --> 19:05.060
you're way back to your base camp you might get shot down.

19:05.060 --> 19:07.580
Before we would shoot maybe half our load here to clear our weapon.

19:07.580 --> 19:08.580
Plus we'd cross-train.

19:08.580 --> 19:11.580
I would be shooting the M79 and getting used to it.

19:11.580 --> 19:15.220
Nothing I would be moving from his rifle over to the machine gun.

19:15.220 --> 19:18.860
So we cross-train so that if one person went down somebody else could also use that weapon.

